{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>BirA acts both as a biotin ligase and a biotin-operon repressor. In the presence of ATP, BirA activates biotin to form the BirA-biotinyl-5'-adenylate (BirA-bio-5'-AMP) or holoBirA complex. HoloBirA can either transfer the biotinyl moiety to the biotin carboxyl carrier protein (BCCP) subunit of acetyl-CoA carboxylase, or bind to the biotin operator site and inhibit transcription of the operon [[cite:PUB00074138], [cite:PUB00074139], [cite:PUB00074140], [cite:PUB00074141]]. The switch between the enzymatic activity and the repressor activity of BirA is regulated by cellular demand for biotin. In conditions of high biotin demand, holoBirA associates with apoBCCP and transfers biotin from bio-5'-AMP to apoBCCP. In conditions of low biotin demand, holoBirA dimerises and binds the biotin operator [[cite:PUB00074187]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure {"accession" "6ndl", "name" "Crystal structure of Staphylococcus aureus biotin protein ligase in complex with a sulfonamide inhibitor"}, :overlaps-with [{"accession" "IPR045864", "name" "Class II Aminoacyl-tRNA synthetase/Biotinyl protein ligase (BPL) and lipoyl protein ligase (LPL)", "type" "homologous_superfamily"}], :member-databases {"hamap" {"MF_00978" "Bifunctional ligase/repressor BirA [birA]"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Bifunctional ligase/repressor BirA", "short" "Bifunct_BirA"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 26, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 2818, "taxa" 12413, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 12971, "sets" 0, "proteins" 12971, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 10073}, "pathways" 0}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {"ec" {"displayName" "ENZYME", "description" "ENZYME is a repository of information relative to the nomenclature of enzymes. It is primarily based on the recommendations of the Nomenclature Committee of the I